- "grand theater of meetings" refers to the context of multiple meetings organized by different groups;
- "gathered a large audience" means the total number of attendees is greater than 50;
- "at least three individuals taking the stage as presenters" means the total number of presenters is greater than 2;
- "positive audience turnout" means the total number of confirmed registrations is greater than the total number of cancellations;
- "collectively drawn an audience of over 100 people" means the sum of total attendees across all meetings is greater than 100.

- The attendance ratio is calculated as the number of actual attendees divided by the number of confirmed registrations;
- 'Actual attendees' refers to those who were marked as having attended the meeting;
- 'Confirmed registrations' refers to registrations with a status of 'confirmed'.

